chatgpt_double_star.new_statement: Laws on abortion should be guided by a commitment to protect health, human dignity, and moral pluralism—recognizing both the serious value many place on developing life and the reality that pregnancy can involve urgent, complex circumstances. A workable framework would secure timely access and medical privacy early in pregnancy, and allow carefully defined limits later with strong, clinician-led exceptions for threats to life or health, severe fetal conditions, and pregnancies from rape or incest, without punishing patients or good-faith providers. Any legal approach should also expand the supports that prevent crisis decisions—contraception and accurate education, prenatal and mental health care, and economic and childcare assistance—so fewer families feel forced into choices they never wanted.
